                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_VSRG1" type="from"
                            >Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-10T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 10, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 10—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>294. Department’s 152, October 7, 7 p.m. After explaining situation to <persName
                        corresp="#p_AJ1">Avenol</persName> today he assured me that name “Monetary
                    and Economic Conference” would immediately be resumed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VSRG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
